An Entrance to the Maze
You stand at the entrance to a dark and foreboding maze. To the North a sandstone passegeway leads into the maze itself. You are surrounded by writhing vines and dense greenery that block all other exits. Nestled in the moss that carpets the ground lie a large boulder with an elaborately decorated plaque and a battered brass lantern. Beside the entrance to the passageway is a pine wood bookshelf.
