An East Garden
You are standing in a resplendent graden. The carefully curated flower beds are marvelous to behold. Just a few of the flowers you can see include marigolds, dandelions, daisies, yellow tulips, daffodils, sunflowers, begonias, and many more. The garden is ringed by tall green hedges, with an exit to the NorthWest. In the middle of the graden sits a simple yet elegant and strangely unsettling statue. The statue depicts a starving man desperately reaching out with open hands.
